      <Description>Images and movies from each of the STEREO SECCHI
(Sun Earth Connection Coronal and Heliospheric Investigation)
telescopes (EUVI, COR1, COR2, HI), with images at the cadence
appropriate to each telescope and mode (4 min to 2 hrs).  Images
are available at each of three resolutions (256^2, 512^2, 1024^2)
and are current to within about three days.</Description>
      <Acknowledgement>From the SECCHI page at NRL:
Please note that all of the SECCHI data is free for public use,
but if you use them in presentations, published work, websites,
etc, please give the appropriate image credits ("STEREO/SECCHI"
will usually suffice).</Acknowledgement>
